description.narrative: UNICEF strengthened child protection (CP) systems by supporting Government of Egypt to adopt, amend, and operationalize child-friendly laws/policies. Technical/financial support and advocacy contributed to adopting law criminalizing Female Genital Mutilation (FGM) medicalization, introducing amendments to Child Law on judicial treatment and alternative care, addressing the intersection between violence against women (VAW) and violence against children (VAC) in Personal Status Law and promoting a newly-drafted alternative care law. Policy change was complemented with launching the Alternative Care Strategy, developing M&E and costed framework of EVAC National Plan of Action (NAP), and operationalizing Annex SOPs on children on the move (COM). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/01/2022
